Enhancement of efficiency in dye-sensitized solar cells  In a dye-sensitized solar cell (DSSC), solar radiation is absorbed by a photosensitive dye, usually a ruthenium complex, bound to a photoanode enriched with a thin film of TiO2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
