				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\sim 80$$\end{document} compared to an unstructured Si film was achieved.

Recently, interference phenomena generating anapole modes in high-refractive index nanoparticles arranged in planar metasurfaces were exploited for sensing [419]. In particular, nanostructured metasurfaces of periodic arrays of nanocuboids on a glass substrate supporting anapole mode were properly designed such that a resonance with ultrahigh Q-factor above one million could be excited at the target infrared wavelength of 1.55μm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
